<Author>Irishtoo
<Content>Loved the hotel, the location a bit less. I spent 4 nights in the Four Seasons in mid December, at the start of a month long holiday in Mexico. I booked about a week before my arrival, via the hotel website, and got a very good (50%)discount on normal rates.I am a sole female traveller, and as it was my first visit, and because my flight arrived at 10pm, I booked the hotel transfer service. I was glad I did! It was very efficient and comfortable. I did not think the cost was unreasonable, especially compared to the costs in other FS hotels.The hotel itself is pretty much what you would expect from the Four Seasons, same bathroom tiles, same toiletries, similar decor, but still very comfortable nonetheless. The deluxe rooms are really very spacious, especially for one person. The windows actually open, and if you have a courtyard view (as I did), it is very pleasant to feel fresh air in the mornings.I had the buffet breakfast every day in the courtyard, and it is a very relaxing start to the day. The mornings in December are very fresh and pleasant before the heat of the day sets in, and the courtyard is exceptionally pleasant, with a chiminea style gas fire in the middle of the dining area, to take the chill off. There are white fairy lights strung through the low hedging which makes it very attractive in the evenings.The staff were, without exception, very helpful, and spoke very good English, for those of us with faltering Spanish.The only minor gripe is that housekeeping was a little eratic. One day I got back to the hotel at about 3-4pm, after a day sightseeing, and the room was not made up. Equally, the turndown tended to be a little late, and once did not happen at all. This is a very minor issue for me, and was quickly remedied with a call to housekeeping.The location is good during the day. It is a pleasant walk to the nearby museums  galleries, and a short walk to the Sevilla metro (which I used extensively and had no problems with). In the evenings however, you would need to take a taxi to a restaurant/bar, as none are within reasonable walking distance. Overall, this was a very comfortable experience, and I would not hesitate to stay here again. 
